nt</a></li><li><a href="/connect-experience/">The CONNECT Experience</a></li><li><a href="/grouplink/">Group Link is Coming!</a></li><li><a href="/baptisms--redirect/">Get Baptized</a></li><li><a href="/adult-ministry-lifelearning--redirect/">Discover Liife Learning: Classes &amp; Groups</a></li><li><a href="/outreach/">Serve in the Community</a></li><li><a href="/giving/">Give Generously</a></li><li><a href="/theprayerwall/">Submit a Prayer Need</a></li></ul></div><hr><h4><img src="http://www.pcctoday.com/monkimage.php?mediaDirectory=mediafiles&amp;mediaId=2263523&amp;fileName=graphic--icon--connect-step-number-1-0-0-74-101.png" width="74" height="101" alt="GRAPHIC : ICON : Connect Step Number 1" title="GRAPHIC : ICON : Connect Step Number 1" style="margin-right: 25px; margin-bottom: 25px;">Attend a Celebration Service</h4><p>We place a high priority on our two identical <a href="/services/"><strong>Celebration Services</strong></a> each Sunday at 9:00 and 10:45 AM. Worshiping and learning in community with others is one of the best ways to re-align yourself with God.&nbsp;</p><p>Consider this a personal invitation to join us at one of our upcoming&nbsp;<strong><a href="https://pcctalks.wufoo.com/forms/meet-n-greet-rsvp-for-july-21">Meet &lsquo;N Greets</a></strong>&nbsp;after the&nbsp;<a href="http://www.pcctoday.com/services/" title="Sunday Services 9:00 or 10:45 AM">10:45 AM service</a>. It is here you can spend a few moments with some of our leadership in an "open House" format. Our next Meet 'N Greets are: September 22, November 17.<a href="https://pcctalks.wufoo.com/forms/meet-n-greet-rsvp-for-july-21/" target="_blank"><br></a></p><hr><h4><img src="http://www.pcctoday.com/monkimage.php?mediaDirectory=mediafiles&amp;mediaId=2263527&amp;fileName=graphic--icon--connect-step-number-2-0-0-74-101.png" width="74" height="101" alt="GRAPHIC : ICON : Connect Step Number 2" title="GRAPHIC : ICON : Connect Step Number 2" style="margin-right: 25px; margin-bottom: 25px;">Read the Bible</h4><p>As we read God&rsquo;s Word we begin to see how God responds to life issues and the people around him. Then when we face similar situations as Jesus did, we begin to respond in the same way. This year the entire church is reading through the New Testament using the <a href="/ministries/bible-reading-plan/">5 X 5 X 5 Bible Reading Plan.</a> &nbsp;Check out this excellent plan [<a href="http://www.pcctoday.com/article/2013-bible-reading-plan-its-simplejust-5-x-5-x-5/">here</a>]. You can also read along as&nbsp;<a href="http://www.raynoah.com" target="_blank">Pastor Ray blogs through each passage.</a> You won't want to miss some of his profound insights!</p><hr><h4><img src="http://www.pcctoday.com/monkimage.php?mediaDirectory=mediafiles&amp;mediaId=2263529&amp;fileName=graphic--icon--connect-step-number-3-0-0-74-101.png" width="74" height="101" alt="GRAPHIC : ICON : Connect Step Number 3" title="GRAPHIC : ICON : Connect Step Number 3" style="margin-right: 25px; margin-bottom: 25px;">Pray</h4><p>Prayer is all about two-way communication. Jesus said, &ldquo;Where two or three are gathered in my name, there I am in the midst of them (Matt. 18:20). Practice daily prayer and joining others in one of our many prayer venues. You can also stay informed of the prayer needs of our church or submit your own prayer request at&nbsp;<a href="/theprayerwall/">The Prayer Wall</a>.&nbsp;</p><hr><h4><img src="http://www.pcctoday.com/monkimage.php?mediaDirectory=mediafiles&amp;mediaId=2263543&amp;fileName=graphic--icon--connect-step-number-4-0-0-74-101.png" width="74" height="101" alt="GRAPHIC : ICON : Connect Step Number 4" title="GRAPHIC : ICON : Connect Step Number 4">Join a Class or Small Group</h4><p>Whether it is a&nbsp;<a href="/adult-ministry-lifelearning--redirect/">class</a>&nbsp;or a&nbsp;<a href="/ministries/adult-education/community-life-small-groups/">small group</a>, there are many opportunities to grow and learn together.&nbsp; Be brave&mdash;jump in! &nbsp;Life Learning <a href="/ministries/adult-education/">classes</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href="/ministries/adult-education/community-life-small-groups/">groups</a>&nbsp;are offered throughout the week on campus and in host homes. New classes begin every quarter and you are welcome to jump in at any time. &nbsp;See our schedule [<a href="/ministries/adult-education/">here]</a>.</p><p>A simple way to find your way into our church family is to participate in a "come and go" 4-week STARTING POINT from 10:15 to 10:45 AM. This "first experience" opportunity is warmly hosted by Doug and Sherrie MacLardy in the Hospitality Room. Learn more about STARTING POINT.</p><hr><h4><img src="http://www.pcctoday.com/monkimage.php?mediaDirectory=mediafiles&amp;mediaId=2263547&amp;fileName=graphic--icon--connect-step-number-5-0-0-74-101.png" width="74" height="101" alt="GRAPHIC : ICON : Connect Step Number 5" title="GRAPHIC : ICON : Connect Step Number 5">Give Selflessly</h4><p>Giving of your&nbsp;<a href="/outreach/">time, talents,</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href="/giving/" target="_blank">treasures</a>&nbsp;pleases the heart of God and fulfills your purpose on this earth. God has a ministry for every one of His children and a mission He has specifically called you to to advance His kingdom. When you selflessly serve with your&nbsp;<a href="/outreach/">time</a>, your&nbsp;<a href="/outreach/">abilities</a>, and your&nbsp;<a href="/giving/">treasure&nbsp;</a>you glorify God.&nbsp;We have many opportunities to <a href="/connect-experience/">discover your gifts</a>, <a href="/giving/">learn about giving generously</a>, and <a href="/outreach/">finding a place to serve</a> in our church, our city, and around the world.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>||5-simple-ways-to-connect-and-grow||||||||http://www.pcctoday.com/monkimage.php?mediaDirectory=mediafiles&mediaId=2308053&fileName=header--connect--main-header-50-50-0-0.jpg~~Patti Arn Memorial Fund Helps Widows and Orphans||||On July 19 we lost a very special friend of Portland Christian Center. In memory of Patti Arn, her friends and family have initiated the Patti Arn Memorial Fund...||||Jul 24 2013||<h2><a href="http://petrosnetwork.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/patti-arn.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-3870" alt="patti arn" src="http://petrosnetwork.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/patti-arn-201x300.jpg" width="201" height="300" /></a></h2>
<p class="highlight">Patti Arn Memorial Fund</p>
<h3 style="text-align: left;" align="center"><i>Widows and Orphans in Africa</i></h3>
<p>In Memory of <strong>Patti Arn</strong>&nbsp;the family has initiated the Patti Arn Memorial Fund. &nbsp;Donations are being directed to build the Women&rsquo;s Development Center in Ethiopia, Africa.&nbsp;<strong>Patti</strong>&nbsp;was using her gifts and talents to help develop a product that could be merchandised here in the states as a sustainability project for widowed women.&nbsp; Most of the women involved were not older than 42 years of age and all of the women have children. &nbsp;As the most poor of Africa the children of these women are unable to go to school because their days are spent on the streets helping to provide for the family through casual labor.</p>
<p><strong>Patti Arn</strong> had personally sponsored a widow, who actually ended up being healed of cancer.&nbsp; We thought that was a sign of her healing as well.</p>
<p>It is a privilege to carry on caring for the poor in honor of our good friend. In an effort to break the chronic cycle of poverty the Women&rsquo;s Development Center provides micro-grants, along with training, to start sustainable small businesses and meaningful work in Africa.&nbsp; The Women&rsquo;s Development Center will house a sewing and craft center along with a training center, internet cafe and bakery.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.egsnetwork.com/gift/gift.php?giftid=6E2B75A3-A276-4B94-A136-26B625C462EC" class="button">Patti Arn Memorial Gift</a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<hr />
<p><a title="Helping Vulnerable Women Help Their Families" href="http://petrosnetwork.org/relief-development/widows/" target="_blank">Learn More about helping widows and orphans in Africa &gt;&gt;</a></p>
<h3>Why Invest in Women? Because They Reinvest In Their Families!</h3>
<blockquote>No one works harder to end hunger than a mother with a hungry child.&nbsp;Research has discovered income earned and controlled by women is directly channeled to their children, who eat better, get healthier and stay in school longer. As a powerful solution for change, investing in widowed women, along with the added value of education and life-skill development not only builds families&rsquo; well-being, self worth and self-confidence, but has<b> the power to break the cycle of chronic poverty.</b></blockquote>
<p>At Petros Network we are reaching for an extraordinary dream&hellip;a world free from chronic hunger and poverty to a life of thriving. And, our efforts are matched by the hardworking mothers who are determined to feed their children, safeguard their health and end their poverty.</p>
<hr />||patti-arn-memorial-fund-helps-widows-and-orphans||||||||~~Guest Speaker: Fouad Masri||<img src="http://f049e6c6bc51d6086828-1f3d9bf827f6f62072870f1ea348709c.r40.cf2.rackcdn.com/uploaded/h/0e2284629_1373651475_header--article--guest-speaker--fouad-masri.jpg" alt="" />||Sunday, July 28th, author and lecturer Fouad Masri returns to Portland Christian Center for our 9:00 and 10:45 AM Celebration Services. Fouad was born and raised in the war zone of Beirut, Lebanon. ...||||Jul 12 2013||<p class="highlight">On Sunday, July 28, Portland Christian Center has the privilege of having special guest Fouad Masri speak during our Celebration Services at 9:00 &amp; 10:45 AM.</p>
<p>Author and lecturer, Fouad Masri, was born and raised in the war zone of Beirut, Lebanon. As a third generation pastor, he has a passion for sharing the love of Christ with Muslims and has spent most of his life doing just that. &nbsp;After coming to the United States to attend seminary, Fouad realized the urgency for teaching American Christians to reach out to our rapidly growing population of internationals, particularly Muslims.</p>
<blockquote>Our job is not to make the Muslim a Christian. Our job is to show them the love of Christ.</blockquote>
<p>Fouad Masri is an ordained minister who has been ministering to Muslims since 1979.&nbsp;He has trained more than 18,000 Christians to sensitively and purposefully share their faith with Muslims through both the <em>Bridges One-Day</em> and <em>Sahara Challenge</em> training programs.&nbsp;In 1989, he founded the <a href="http://www.crescentproject.org">Crescent Project</a> to nurture transformational relationships between Christians and Muslims and overcome misconceptions about Islam and Christianity.&nbsp;He has served as a guest instructor at universities and Christian ministries and has been featured in media publications, including Christianity Today, Newsweek, Mission Network News, and on CBN, TBN, the Janet Parshall Show, and Prime Time America.</p>
<h4>An Important Message for Our Cross-Cultural Training</h4>
<p>Fouad Masri returns to Portland Christian Center on Sunday, July 28th for our 9:00 and 10:45 AM Celebration services.&nbsp;He will share the real-life transformations which can occur in our community as we all learn more about our Muslim neighbors and <a href="/taking-the-fear-out-of-islam/">Take The Fear Out of Islam</a>. This is an important addition to our month of July cross cultural training on Wednesday nights with fellow Muslim expert and trainer, Samuel Hakim.</p>||guest-speaker-fouad-masri||||||||http://www.pcctoday.com/monkimage.php?mediaDirectory=mediafiles&mediaId=2287995&fileName=header--article--guest-speaker--fouad-masri-50-50-0-0.jpg~~Children's Volunteer of the Month - June||<img src="http://f049e6c6bc51d6086828-1f3d9bf827f6f62072870f1ea348709c.r40.cf2.rackcdn.com/uploaded/h/0e735137_header--get-connected--children--home.jpg" alt="" />||Adventure Kids, the dynamic children's program of Portland Christian Center (Portland, Oregon) has been blessed with incredible volunteers who serve in a variety of children's activities and ...||||Jun 14 2013||<p>Adventure Kids, the dynamic children's program of Portland Christian Center (Portland, Oregon) has been blessed with incredible volunteers who serve in a variety of children's activities and programs within the children's department.</p><p>Last Sunday, we honored Dave and Krissy Fillis as our Adventure Kids Volunteers of the Month. Both Dave and Krissy have actively and faithfully served our children's ministries since coming into the church five years ago. They currently team lead our Royal Ranger Clubs for boys and Mpact clubs for girls on Wednesday evenings.&nbsp;</p><p><img src="http://f049e6c6bc51d6086828-1f3d9bf827f6f62072870f1ea348709c.r40.cf2.rackcdn.com/uploaded/p/0e2220705_1371230100_profile--volunteer--dave-and-krissy-fillis.jpg" alt="Profile : Volunteer : Dave and Krissy Fillis" title="Profile : Volunteer : Dave and Krissy Fillis"><strong>Thank you, Dave and Krissy,</strong> for your dedicated leadership. Your initiative, commitment and passion for your students and leaders is invaluable!</p><p><a href="/ministries/children/" class="button">About Adventure Kids</a></p><p><a href="http://www.pcctoday.com/ministries/children/serving-opportunities-with-children/" class="button">Ways You Can Serve!</a></p>||childrens-volunteer-of-the-month-june||||||||http://www.pcctoday.com/monkimage.php?mediaDirectory=mediafiles&mediaId=393842&fileName=header--get-connected--children--home-50-50-0-0.jpg~~The Christian Response to Muslims||<img src="http://f049e6c6bc51d6086828-1f3d9bf827f6f62072870f1ea348709c.r40.cf2.rackcdn.com/uploaded/h/0e2173805_header--2013--taking-the-fear-out-of-islam.jpg" alt="" />||Christians have been asking many questions about Muslims.  Who are they and what do they believe? Do all Muslims sanction violence?  Most importantly, what attitude should Christians have toward ...||||Jun 10 2013||<h3 class="highlight"><a href="/taking-the-fear-out-of-islam/" target="_blank">Taking the Fear Out of Islam</a>&nbsp;(<a href="/taking-the-fear-out-of-islam/" target="_blank">Cross Cultural Training Seminar</a>)</h3>
<p><a href="/taking-the-fear-out-of-islam/" target="_blank"><strong>Date: &nbsp;</strong>Wednesdays, July 10, 17, 24, 31 ~ </a><a href="/taking-the-fear-out-of-islam/" target="_blank">7:00 to 8:30 PM</a><br /><a href="/taking-the-fear-out-of-islam/" target="_blank"><strong>Guest Speaker: &nbsp;</strong>Samuel Hakim</a><br /><a href="/taking-the-fear-out-of-islam/" target="_blank"><strong>Location: &nbsp;</strong>Portland Christian Center</a></p>
<p>Fun and creative activities for children and teens are provided during workshop times.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><a href="/taking-the-fear-out-of-islam/" class="button">More Information</a></p>
<h2>Article: The Christian Response to Islam</h2>
<p><em>Reprinted from <a href="http://voiceofchristmedia.org/index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=155:the-christian-response-to-muslims-v15-155&amp;catid=38&amp;Itemid=264" title="Voice of Christ Media">Voice of Christ Media Ministries</a>&nbsp;</em></p>
<p>Christians have been asking many questions about Muslims.&nbsp; Who are they and what do they believe?</p>
<p>Do all Muslims sanction violence?&nbsp; Most importantly, what attitude should Christians have toward them?&nbsp; Why do some Muslims use the Koran to justify violence while others condemn it?</p>
<p>These are all important questions.</p>
<p><strong>Overcoming Stereotypes</strong></p>
<p><strong></strong>It is important to understand that not all Muslims are terrorists. In fact, only a small number of them promote violence. Most are decent, peace-loving people.</p>
<p>Some are quite secular in their outlook and way of life. They claim to be Muslims but do not faithfully practice their religion. They may not even know much about its teachings. Other moderate Muslims believe Islam is just a religion and try to practice it faithfully. Most are peace loving and generally only use peaceful persuasion to make converts. They are often embarrassed by acts of terrorism that are carried out in the name of Islam.</p>
<p>Fundamentalist Muslims, on the other hand, have a political as well as a religious agenda. They believe everyone should live in submission to Islamic law. They take the teaching of the Koran and Mohammed's commands to fight for the cause of Allah literally and believe violence is justified for taking control of the world.</p>
<p><strong>Wrong and Right Responses to Muslims</strong></p>
<p>Muslims around the world are watching to see how Christians respond to them. How we react to them may very well determine whether we draw attention to the Gospel or obscure it.</p>
<p>We have an unprecedented opportunity to reach out to Muslims by demonstrating the love of Christ.&nbsp; This is not to say that we must close our eyes and simply overlook acts of violence. Scripture teaches that those in authority have been empowered by God to punish the responsible ones (I Peter 2:13-14).</p>
<p>But, individually, we must never respond with hatred or revenge. To do so is not the way of Christ. "For you have been called for this purpose, since Christ also suffered for you, leaving you an example for you to follow in His steps. While being reviled, He did not revile in return; while suffering, He uttered no threats, but kept entrusting Himself to Him who judges righteously" (I Peter 2:21, 23).</p>
<p>In his editorial in the October 27, 2001, issue of World magazine, John Piper said it well when he warned of the danger of falling into the sin of hatred.</p>
<p>"The spirit of revenge sends the false signal that Christ is not an all-sufficient, all-satisfying Savior. We justify our own little jihad, and seek our satisfaction by injuring the adversary. But true Christians treasure Jesus above vengeance."</p>
<p>However, neither is it right to cave in to the shrill voices that are preaching a warped view of tolerance and saying that all religions, including Islam, lead to God. Piper said this emphasis is equally wrong.</p>
<p>"In reaction against indiscriminate hate there is now a stampede to pluralism and twisted tolerance. If Muslims are hated, then let us call ecumenical gatherings, and let us all praise the virtues of Islam and the wisdom of Allah and the goodness of Mohammed. But let no one speak the intolerable and indispensable truth that Jesus is the only way to God."</p>
<p>Jesus clearly said, "I am the way, and the truth, and the life. No one comes to the Father but through me" (John 14:6). We should never hesitate to boldly say that the only way to God is through the Lord Jesus Christ.</p>
<p>To react to Muslims by falling into these equally wrong traps of hatred and tolerance is to hide the message of eternal life from them. Both of these attitudes are wrong and keep Muslims in spiritual darkness. Let us stand against these sins and instead focus on lovingly sharing with them the message of salvation through Jesus Christ and His finished work on the Cross.</p>
<p><strong>Loving in Jesus' Name</strong></p>
<p>You can make a huge difference by praying for Muslim nations and individuals in them. In fact, when fear begins to grip your mind, stop and pray for Muslims -- even those who promote terrorism!! Pray for Muslims to have open hearts and for the Gospel to reach them. Ask God to raise up workers to help evangelize Muslim countries. Pray for those like the Voice of Christ Media team who are already doing this.</p>
<p>Then ask God to use you to befriend and evangelize the Muslims you know. Show them practical love. Be loving and humble. Don't advocate a particular culture or political agenda. Focus on Jesus Christ and His uniqueness. Offer to study the life of Christ with them by reading through one of the Gospels. Ask God to give them spiritual understanding and to draw them to faith in Christ.</p>
<p>Jesus Christ is the only answer. Ask God to show you what part He wants you to have in evangelizing Muslims. Trust Him to use you to reach out to them with loving, courageous witness.</p>
<h6>Register for the upcoming Cross-Cultural Training Workshop, Taking the Fear Out of Islam <a href="https://secure.accessacs.com/access/eventlogin.aspx?id=fx1QmbWhp1ISbeQycSXQHQ==&amp;site=1233&amp;ReturnUrl=events%2fwz_people.aspx&amp;ChurchID=3183&amp;EventID=49899&amp;sn=1233" target="_blank">right here.</a></h6>||the-christian-response-to-muslims||||||||http://www.pcctoday.com/monkimage.php?mediaDirectory=mediafiles&mediaId=2211689&fileName=header--2013--taking-the-fear-out-of-islam-50-50-0-0.jpg~~Congratulations 2013 Graduates||<img src="http://f049e6c6bc51d6086828-1f3d9bf827f6f62072870f1ea348709c.r40.cf2.rackcdn.com/uploaded/h/0e2203997_header--2013-graduates.jpg" alt="" />||The Portland Christian Center family would like to extend our heart-felt congratulations to our 2013 high school and college graduates. This milestone represents years of hard work and dedication. ...||||Jun 07 2013||<p>The Portland Christian Center family would like to extend our heart-felt congratulations to our 2013 high school and college graduates. This milestone represents years of hard work and dedication. Congratulations! May the Lord bless and guide you as you take the next steps of your journey.</p><h3>Our 2013 High School Graduates<br><br></h3><p><img src="http://www.pcctoday.com/monkimage.php?mediaDirectory=mediafiles&amp;mediaId=2232621&amp;fileName=graphic--photo--grad--shelby-baugus-0-0-100-150.jpg" width="100" height="150" alt="GRAPHIC : PHOTO : GRAD : Shelby Baugus" title="GRAPHIC : PHOTO : GRAD : Shelby Baugus" style="float: left; margin: 1px 8px;"><span class="highlight">Shelby Baugus</span><br> Shelby is graduating from Horizon Christian High School. In the fall, she will be attending the University of Portland, majoring in Nursing.</p><p><br><br><br><br><img src="http://www.pcctoday.com/monkimage.php?mediaDirectory=mediafiles&amp;mediaId=2232625&amp;fileName=graphic--photo--grad--emily-becker-0-0-100-150.jpg" width="100" height="150" alt="GRAPHIC : PHOTO : GRAD : 