<h3>5x5x5 Bible Reading Plan</h3>
<h5>Reading through the New Testament in 2013<br />5 minutes &nbsp;| &nbsp;5 days &nbsp;| &nbsp;5 ways</h5>
<p>Beginning January 1st, the families of Portland Christian Center will begin a journey through the New Testament using Discipleship Journal's 5x5x5 Bible Reading Plan. Will you join the journey? You may print the detailed plan, or access the plan on-line with YouVersion.</p>
<p><a href="http://f049e6c6bc51d6086828-1f3d9bf827f6f62072870f1ea348709c.r40.cf2.rackcdn.com/uploaded/2/0e769073_2013-bible-reading-plan.pdf" class="button">Printable Version</a> <a href="https://www.youversion.com/reading-plans/232-discipleship-journals-5x5x5-reading-plan" class="button" target="_blank">YouVersion</a> <a href="http://raynoah.com" class="button" target="_blank">Pastor Ray's Daily Blog</a></p>
<hr />
<h3>How it works:</h3>
<h4>5 minutes a day</h4>
<p>Start with reading 5 minutes a day. This reading plan will take you through all 260 chapters of the New Testament, one chapter per day. The gospels are read throughout the year to keep the story of Jesus fresh all year.</p>
<h4>5 days a week</h4>
<p>Determine a time and location to spend 5 minutes a day for 5 days each week. It is best to have a consistent time and a quiet place where you can regularly meet with the Lord.</p>
<h4>5 ways to dig deeper</h4>
<p>We must pause in our reading to dig into the Bible. Below are five different ways to dig deeper each day. These exercises will encourage meditation. We recommend trying a single idea for a week to find what works best for you. Remember to keep a pen and paper ready to capture God&rsquo;s insights.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Underline or highlight</strong> key words or phrases in the Bible passage. Use a pen or highlighter to mark new discoveries from the text. Periodically review your markings to see what God is teaching you.</li>
<li><strong>Put it into your own words</strong>. Read the passage or verse slowly, then rewrite each phrase or sentence using your own words.</li>
<li><strong>Ask and answer some questions.</strong> Questions unlock new discoveries and meanings. Ask questions about the passage using these words: who, what, why, when, where, or how. Jot down some thoughts on how you would answer these questions.</li>
<li><strong>Capture the big idea.</strong> God&rsquo;s Word communicates big ideas. Periodically ask, <em>What&rsquo;s the big idea in this sentence, paragraph, or chapter?</em></li>
<li><strong>Personalize the meaning.</strong> When God speaks to us through the Scriptures, we must respond. A helpful habit is personalizing the Bible through application. Ask: <em>How could my life be different today as I respond to what I&rsquo;m reading?&nbsp;</em></li>
</ul>||make-2013-count-in-your-spiritual-growth||||||||http://www.pcctoday.com/monkimage.php?mediaDirectory=mediafiles&mediaId=1885655&fileName=header--2013-bible-reading-plan-50-50-0-0.jpg~~Join us at one of our Celebration Services this Sunday!||||This Sunday we return to our regular Celebration Service schedule at 9 and 10:45 AM. There are also several great classes for Children through Adults at both hours as well!||||Dec 19 2012||<p>This Sunday (December 23) we return to our regular Celebration Service schedule at 9:00 and 10:45 AM. There are also several great classes for Children through Adults at both hours as well!</p>||join-us-at-one-of-our-celebration-services-this-sunday||||||||~~Day 31 Devotional - Praying for our Family/Relatives||<img src="http://f049e6c6bc51d6086828-1f3d9bf827f6f62072870f1ea348709c.r40.cf2.rackcdn.com/uploaded/h/0e766919_header--worship--31-days-of-prayer.jpg" alt="" />||Did you know God has given you everything you need for life and godliness? Be encouraged today that He has his watchful eye on you. Today we, as a church, continue our 31 Days of Prayer by praying ...||PCC Communications Team||Oct 31 2012||<blockquote>
<h4>QUOTE OF THE DAY: Alexis De Tocqueville</h4>
<i>"The Americans combine the notions of Christianity and liberty so intimately in their minds that it is impossible to make them conceive one without the other."<strong> - A French Politician, Thinker, and Historian (1805 - 1859)</strong></i></blockquote>
<h5>2 Peter 1:3-11</h5>
<p><b>His divine power has given us everything we need for life and godliness through our knowledge of Him who called us by his own glory and goodness...For this reason, make every effort to add to your faith and goodness, knowledge, self-control, perseverance, godliness, brotherly kindess, love. But if anyone does not have them, he is nearsighted and blind, and has forgotten that he has been cleansed from his past sins...be all the more eager to make your calling and election sure. For if you do these things, you will never fall, and you will receive a rich welcome into the eternal kingdom of our Lord and Savior Jesus Christ.</b></p>
<hr />
<h5>REFLECT AND DISCUSS</h5>
<p><b>What new efforts do you think you need to make to add to your faith in the coming days, weeks, and months?</b></p>
<hr />
<h5>PRAYER</h5>
<p><i>Your divine power has given us everything we need for life and godliness through our knowledge of Him who called us by His own glory and goodness. Through these very great and precious promises we may participate in Your divine nature. Visit Your divine nature upon us and our nation so that we may escape the corruption in the world caused by evil desires. We desire to make our calling and election sure so we will never fall, and receive a rich welcome into the eternal kingdom of our Lord and Savior Jesus Christ. </i></p>
<p><i>Lord Jesus, Come Heal Our Land, so that all men will praise Your Name...Amen</i></p>
